cmd-blacklist-add-help:
Adds a user or a role to the guild's blacklist.
Blacklisted users in the guild cannot use my commands.
cmd-blacklist-remove-help: Removes a user or a role from the guild's blacklist.
cmd-kick-help: Kicks a user from the server.
cmd-ban-help: Bans a user from the server.
cmd-hackban-help: Bans a user from the server with their ID.
cmd-welcome-help:
Enables a message that will be sent to a channel when someone joins the server.
If you specify a picture url in your message, it will automatically hide your link.
In your messages you can use the following keywords and they will be replaced :

{user.name} : User name
{user.mention} : User mention
{server.name} : Server name
{user.id} : User ID
{server_member_count} : Number of users in the server
cmd-welcome-welcome_off-help: Disables the welcome message in the channel.
cmd-goodbye-help:
Enables a message that will be sent to a channel when someone leaves the server.
If you specify a picture url in your message, it will automatically hide your link.
In your messages you can use the following keywords and they will be replaced :

{user.name} : User name
{user.mention} : User mention
{server.name} : Server name
{user.id} : User ID
{server_member_count} : Number of users in the server
cmd-goodbye-goodbye_off-help: Disables the goodbye message in the channel.
cmd-autorole-help: Sets autoroles for new members of the server.
cmd-autorole-set-help: Adds an autorole for new members of the server.
cmd-autorole-now-help: Displays the current autoroles in the server.
cmd-autorole-reset-help: Removes every current autoroles in the server.
cmd-autorole-remove-help: Removes an autorole from the current autoroles in the server.
cmd-joinclan-help: Allows one to get a role. You cannot have multiple clans at the same time.
cmd-clan-add-help: Allows one to add a clan to the server, members can join it with joinclan
cmd-clan-delete-help: Allows one to delete a clan of this server.
cmd-clan-list-help: Displays the available clans in the server.
cmd-8ball-help: Gives a random answer to your question.
cmd-ily-help: If you want to know if I love you.
cmd-roll-help:
Generates a random number between 0 and the max specifed.
Can also generate a random number between two numbers.
Otherwise it'll generate a random number between 0 and 100.
cmd-flip-help: Flips a coin if no user is specified, otherwise it flips a user.
cmd-dog-help: Displays a random picture of a dog.
cmd-cat-help: Displays a random picture of a cat.
cmd-customcommand-help:
Manages the custom commands in the server.
You can also create your own command, for more information use help cc add.

- Image links in custom commands are automatically hidden.
cmd-customcommand-add-help:
Allows one to add a custom command to the server.
By putting >>> at the beginning, the custom command will run the selected command.
By putting && between commands, every command will be launched together.
cmd-customcommand-raw-help: Displays the content of a custom command.
cmd-customcommand-edit-help: Allows one to edit a custom command that already exists in the server.
cmd-customcommand-delete-help: Allows one to delete a custom command in the server.
cmd-ascii-help: Displays a text in ascii art.
cmd-poll-help: Interactively creates a poll with the following question.
cmd-meme-help:
Generates a meme.
It displays your text on a user's avatar or on a custom picture.
cmd-osu-help:
Displays information about an osu! profile.
You can choose a mode, if you don't specify any mode, standard is used.
Mode list : Standard, Taiko, Ctb, Mania
cmd-choice-help:
Randomly selects an option between multiple options.
By putting >>> at the beginning, it will start the selected command.

- Image links in this command are automatically hidden.
cmd-nextep-help: Displays the remaining time before the next episode of an anime.
cmd-picture-help: Displays my picture commands list. (Powered by weeb.sh and arcadia-api.xyz)
cmd-help-help: Shows my commands or displays help for a command.
cmd-shard-help: Shows which shard you're currently on.
cmd-me-help: Allows one to talk as me.
cmd-avatar-help:
Displays a user's avatar.
If you don't specify a user, it will display your avatar.
cmd-userinfo-help:
Displays information about a user.
If you don't specify a user, it will display your information.
cmd-roleinfo-help: Displays information about a role. Warning, this is case sensitive.
cmd-credits-help: Displays my special thank you list.
cmd-changelog-help:
Displays my last patch notes.
For further information about my old(er) patch notes, visit my official server.
cmd-don-help: Displays information and links to support me.
cmd-id-help:
Displays the ID of a user.
If you don't specify a user, it will display your ID.
cmd-suggestion-help: Sends a suggestion to the developer.
cmd-bug-help: Reports a bug to the developer.
cmd-feedback-help: Sends a feedback about me to the developer.
cmd-giverole-help: Gives a role to a user in the guild.
cmd-setrole-help: Manages which roles can be obtained with the getrole command.
cmd-setrole-add-help: Makes a role obtainable with the getrole command.
cmd-setrole-remove-help: Removes an obtainable role with the getrole command.
cmd-setrole-reset-help: Resets the list of obtainable roles.
cmd-setrole-list-help: Displays every obtainable role with the getrole command.
cmd-getrole-help: Allows a user to get a role or to remove it. Warning, this is case sensitive.
cmd-join-help: Summons me into your voice channel or into the specified one.
cmd-play-help:
Enqueues a song with a url or keyword(s).
Can also enqueue a stream or a radio.
cmd-bind-help: Prevents the usage of commands in every channel except in the one where the command is used.
cmd-stop-help: Stops the player and clears the queue.
cmd-resume-help: Resumes a song if it's currently paused.
cmd-forceskip-help:
Skips the current song without needing to vote.
If you specify a queue position, it skips every song until it reaches the specified position.
cmd-np-help: Returns some information about the current song.
cmd-active-help: Displays all my players with their status.
cmd-volume-help:
Sets the playback volume. Accepted values are from 0 to 1000.
Putting + or - before the volume will make the volume change based on the current volume.
If you don't specify a new volume, it displays the volume it's currently at.
cmd-plstart-help:
Starts an autoplaylist.
If you don't specify an autoplaylist, it loads yours.
cmd-plnew-help: Creates a new autoplaylist that can be loaded.
cmd-plinfo-help: Gives information about an autoplaylist, if you don't specify one, the current autoplaylist's information will be displayed.
cmd-plrepair-help: Repairs an autoplaylist, if you don't specify one, the current autoplaylist will be repaired.
cmd-lyrics-help:
Displays the lyrics of a song.
If you don't specify any url or keywords, it displays the current song's lyrics.
cmd-pladd-help:
Adds a song to the current autoplaylist, if you don't specify a url, it will add the current song to the autoplaylist.
You can use keywords to try adding it without a url.
cmd-plremove-help:
Removes a song from the current autoplaylist, if you don't specify a url, it will remove the current song from the autoplaylist.
You can use keywords to try removing it without a url.
You can specify the position in the autoplaylist (which can be found with plinfo)
cmd-plclear-help:
Deletes an autoplaylist and all of its content.
Warning : This operation cannot be undone.
cmd-plsettings-help:
Displays information about an autoplaylist or edits its settings.
Whitelisted users can repair, add, and remove songs from the autoplaylist.
Everyone can use the autoplaylist(s), even if they are private.
Everyone can add/remove/repair the autoplaylist(s), even if they are not private.
cmd-plclone-help: Creates an autoplaylist by copying an existing autoplaylist.
cmd-promote-help:
Moves a song by specifying the queue index.
If you don't specify a position to move the song to, it will move the song to the first position of the queue.
If you don't specify a song either, it will move the last song of the queue to the first position of the queue.
cmd-remove-help:
Removes a song from the queue.
If you don't specify a position, it will remove the last song in the queue.
Otherwise it will remove a song based on its position in the queue.
You can specify a second position to remove every song between the two positions.
cmd-playnext-help: Enqueues a song to the first position of the queue.
cmd-setdj-help:
Manages DJ roles.
Member(s) with the DJ role can use every musical command.
cmd-setdj-set-help: Adds DJ permissions to a specified role.
cmd-setdj-remove-help: Removes DJ permissions from a specified role.
cmd-setdj-reset-help: Removes DJ permissions from every role in the server.
cmd-setdj-now-help: Displays every role with DJ permissions.
cmd-setdj-all-help: Grants my DJ permissions to everyone in the server.

cmd-perms-info:
**Help with permissions:**
```My permissions are mostly based on your server/channel permissions.

Examples :
- You cannot use the ban command if you cannot ban users.
- You cannot use the purge command if you cannot manage messages.

I'll grant you more functionalities if you're alone in a voice channel with me, or if you have DJ permissions.``````fix
DJ permissions :``````It allows a user to use every musical command without necessarily having high permissions in the server.

To grant DJ permissions to someone, you have to give them a DJ role.``````fix
DJ Role :``````By having this role, a user has the ability to use all musical commands, it grants the same permissions in the case of someone alone in a voice channel with me.

You can set a role as a DJ role with the {}setdj command.
A role called DJ is given DJ permissions by default.```

cmd-bassboost-help:
Changes the player's bass frequencies up to 5 levels. OFF, LOW, MEDIUM, HIGH, INSANE and WTF.
You can use the equalizer to make adjustments as you'd like.
cmd-equalizer-help:
Manages an equalizer with 15 bands. Valid values are from -0.25 to 1.
-0.25 means that the given frequency is completely muted and 0.25 means it is doubled.
Use reactions to interactively move the cursor and edit gains. You can press the circle to reset the equalizer.
Otherwise you can specify a band and a gain to edit it quickly.

cmd-blindtest-help:
Starts a blindtest in the current channel.

Available options:

longestword=true|false (Default to False):
 Accept the longest word as a good answer.

listening=true|false (Default to False):
 Do not accept answers, just listen to the songs.

timeout=number (Default to 120):
 Timeout before stopping the song if not found. Between 3 and 300 seconds.

severity=number (Default to 100):
 Severity in percentage of word to accept an answer. Between 1 and 100%.

percentage=number,number,number (Default to 100,0,0):
 Percentage of OP, ED, OST. The sum of all values should be 100.

wait=number (Default to 5):
 Time to wait before each song. Between 0 and 30 seconds.

argument=status (Default to all):
 Only select a type of watched anime in the given anime lists.
Available status are: all, completed, watching, onhold, dropped, ptw.

remove=status,status2 (Default to ptw):
 Ignore a type (or serveral) of watched anime (separated by commas) in the given anime lists.
Available status are: completed, watching, onhold, dropped, ptw.
